cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper is primarily focused on improving the accuracy and efficiency of deep neural networks for various applications of artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on the ImageNet dataset, which is a popular dataset for computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel DNN architecture, which involves sparsity patterns and hierarchical taxonomy, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of their proposed architecture in natural language processing (NLP), which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
